reviewText: Like several other Wiggles titles this is a remake of an older video but luckilyThe Wiggles - Dance Partyis available on DVD, it's their third video full of charm, self made sets, and Field brothers taking turns as Feathersword. Here Comes the Big Red Car hails from 2006 and the 11 year difference shows in the budget for sets and effects but it loses a star because of the adult annoyance. Are the Wiggles having a concert in front of a green screen? Are they and their friends having a concert in the Wiggle house kitchen? Or is it a beach party? They could have made two videos with a more cohesive theme.I like Paddy as Captain Feathersword in HCBRC better than Anthony's in Dance Party but a part of me wishes his crew would either get their own spin off already or get scurvy. Wiggles videos are supposed to be mostly Wiggles and some of their friends. The introductions to the songs aren't that necessary and the performances feel a bit stale compared to others. At the time Greg was in the midst of his then unknown illness and that might have had some affects too. If your kids are familiar with Sam they might wonder why he's there as a dancer and pirate instead of a proper Wiggle.My copy of this DVD came in the 3 packThe Wiggles - 3 Pack - Car/Time/Dancethe remake of Wiggle Time is better with less effects and Greg's blissful Get Ready to Wiggle. You Make Me Feel Like Dancing with Sam is the third video not the original version of Dance Party. Here Comes the Big Red Car comes with extras, an illustrated story about Anthony painting his room, photos from the shoot, and a couple episodes of Lights Camera Action Wiggles.
summary: Liked it better as Dance Party
